<h2>Machaut: The fount of grace</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Machaut: The fount of grace</dt>
<dd>The Orlando Consort<br>
<i>Hyperion 68417</i> [CD]</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<li>Donnez, signeurs (ballade a3, n26)</li>
<li>Tu qui gregem / Plange regni / Apprehende arma (motet a4,
n22)</li>
<li>Tant doucement me sens emprisonnez (rondeau a2, n9)</li>
<li>Felix virgo / Inviolata genitrix / Ad te suspiramus (motet a4,
n23)</li>
<li>H&eacute;, dame de valour (monophonic virelai, n11)</li>
<li>Tres douce dame (ballade a2, n24)</li>
<li>Je ne cesse de prier &quot;Le lay de la fonteinne&quot; (lay
a3, n16)</li>
<li>Christe qui lux / Veni creator spiritus / Tribulatio proxima
est (motet a4, n21)</li>
<li>En mon cuer a un descort (virelai a2, n24)</li>
<li>Tant doucement me sens emprisonnez (rondeau a4, n9)</li>
</ol></p>

<p>Performers: Matthew Venner (countertenor), Mark Dobell (tenor),
Angus Smith (tenor), Donald Greig (baritone)</p>

<p>Playing time: 63'</p>

<p>Recording date: July 2022 (Essex); released: 2023</p>

<p>Note that Rondeau #9 is usually taken to be a four-voice piece,
per the later sources, so the earlier two-voice version is the
addition here.</p>

